This paper involves the use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) to create paintings, which falls under the category of AI. The paper also mentions the use of computer vision (CV) to learn and inherit the original painting style of the author. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metrics to evaluate the quality of the paintings, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) to consider lexical and phonological similarities of seed words, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (CL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Dadaism and impossibility of improvisation principles, which could potentially fall under the category of graphics (GR).
